<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10183804857620></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10183804857620><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10183804857620>RE: Wis</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10183804857620#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>800 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 9th 3:33 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.79]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are several different items that have the same voodoo doll look when carried. The small wisdom deity (100-200pp in price), which others have already discussed, is one of them, but you shouldn't see anyone carrying it, since it should be in their range slot. If someone has a doll in their hand, it is probably a Paw of Opalla (sp?). This is a +9 wis item, that has ac and some other stats. This item is a 1000pp+ item to purchase, or a rather boring quest to obtain (and also not doable at 14, or anytime soon). <br><br>If you keep ending up in groups that loot FFA (free-for-all), don't be shy. stand up before the mob dies, melee a little, and get in and grab some loot. If anyone complains about the cleric meleeing, suggest they establish a loot order. Common ones in low level groups include: loot to 2(or 3)pp or loot x number of corpses. Masterloot (one person loots all, then splits with the group) gets more common at higher levels, but most new characters are not comfortable with it.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
