	   <tr><td colspan=2>I actually had to do that last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;And this is as a level 45 cleric!  Our dwarf warrior kept chain-pulling regardless of me saying &quot;LOM - hold please&quot; so after a pull with him at 30% health, I left him there.<br><br>Couple times the group said &quot;You need to heal so-and-so&quot; and I said &quot;I will when I am RFP.&quot;  Well, when I did get back to full mana I dropped a cheal on him and resumed medding (fully buffed dwarven tank had over 2k hps) and we went back to pulling.  From then on if I happened to get LOM, he listened...<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-----------<br>Zarros, high elven cleric of Tunare<br>Zraxis, Warrior of Cabilis</td></tr>
